Cape Town - The police have arrested a 21-year-old suspect on charges ranging from hijacking to the possession of stolen property and an illegal firearm. Police spokesperson FC van Wyk said the victim of a hijacking alerted the Flying Squad on Sunday night, close to Mitchells Plain. "(On Monday) morning members attached to Western Cape Flying Squad were alerted by a complainant that he saw his vehicle which was hijacked on Sunday night (2018-07-29) in Eisleben Road near Heinz Park," Van Wyk said. "The members investigated the matter and followed up more leads which led them to the address of a 21-year-old suspect, who was arrested in possession of a rifle with no serial number, a black replica firearm, two cellular telephones and a tablet. The hijacked vehicleâ€™s key was also found in his possession," Van Wyk said. "He is due to appear in the Athlone Magistrate Court once charged for the possession of an illegal firearm and stolen property and hijacking." @CapeTimesSA  ctnews@inl.co.za  Cape Times